        <h1>Third-Party Libraries Memory Leak</h1>
        <div class="description">
            <p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Memory leaks can occur when using third-party libraries, especially if those libraries manage resources like DOM nodes or event listeners and the resources are not properly cleaned up. This can prevent garbage collection and lead to increased memory usage.</p>
            <p><strong>Example Code:</strong></p>
            <pre>
function useThirdPartyLibrary() {
    const elements = [];
    for (let i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {
        const element = document.createElement('div');
        thirdPartyLibrary.manageElement(element); // Hypothetical third-party library call
        elements.push(element); // Accidental reference
    }
}
